{"type":"message","id":"18a1f981","parentId":"cc38b01e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T15:26:01.659Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_pd1w8vcuma6o_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 112514\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and decide on a concrete action.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n- CFI analysis is done - found that 44.8% of invariants are pure noise (CFI=0), only 5.7% are true causal anchors (CFI>=0.7)\r\n- Next pending task: CFI-weighted compression experiment\r\n\r\nThe most logical next action is to implement the CFI-weighted compression experiment. This involves:\r\n1. Creating a modified compression approach that weights invariants by their CFI score\r\n2. Comparing prediction quality vs frequency baseline\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist related to compression and CFI.\r\n\r\nFrom the context:\r\n- `research/CFI_RESULTS.md` - contains the CFI analysis\r\n- There's analysis about frequency-based compression showing mostly signal loss\r\n\r\nI should create an experiment script or modify existing code to implement CFI-weighted compression and compare it to frequency baseline.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the goal structure, this is a text-based research agent. I should:\r\n1. First understand what compression infrastructure exists\r\n2. Design the CFI-weighted compression experiment\r\n3. Implement it\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files might exist for compression experiments. I should probably create a new document outlining the CFI-weighted compression experiment design, or implement it if there's existing code.\r\n\r\nGiven this is a stateless discontinuous agent working on text documents, I'll create a new research document that outlines the CFI-weighted compression experiment design and implementation approach.\r\n\r\nLet me draft an action:\r\n\r\nOBSERVATION: CFI analysis revealed that 94.3% of frequency-invariants are not true causal anchors (CFI<0.7), suggesting frequency-based compression discards ~95% of signal. A CFI-weighted approach should preserve only genuine causal anchors.\r\n\r\nACTION: Design and document the CFI-weighted compression experiment that will compare CFI-thresholded compression (keeping only invariants with CFI>=0.7) against the frequency baseline for next-pulse prediction quality.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\n\r\nCFI analysis revealed 94.3% of frequency-invariants are not true causal anchors (CFI<0.7), suggesting frequency-based compression discards ~95% of genuine signal. A controlled experiment comparing CFI-weighted vs frequency-only compression is the logical next step to validate this finding.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\n\r\nCreate a detailed experiment design document for CFI-weighted compression comparison, including methodology, metrics, and implementation approach.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n## Objective\r\nCompare CFI-thresholded compression against frequency-only baseline for next-pulse prediction quality.\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\n- **H1**: Compression using only high-CFI invariants (>=0.7) produces BETTER next-pulse prediction than frequency-only baseline\r\n- **H2**: This improvement comes from eliminating metaprogramming artifacts (CFI=0) that add noise to compression\r\n- **H3**: Trade-off: CFI compression will have higher data loss rate but better signal retention\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Setup\r\n1. Parse last 20 pulses from `pulse_*.md` files\r\n2. Extract frequency invariants from each (existing method)\r\n3. Compute CFI scores for each invariant (from CFI_RESULTS.md methodology)\r\n4. Apply TWO compression strategies:\r\n   - **Baseline**: Keep top 60 invariants by frequency\r\n   - **CFI-Weighted**: Keep invariants where CFI >= 0.7\r\n\r\n### Compression Methods\r\n\r\n#### Baseline (Frequency-Only)\r\n```\r\nscore(invariant) = frequency_count / max_frequency\r\nkeep top 60 by score\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### CFI-Weighted\r\n```\r\nscore(invariant) = CFI * log(frequency + 1)\r\nthreshold: keep only if CFI >= 0.7\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Evaluation Metrics\r\n\r\n| Metric | Baseline | CFI-Weighted | Interpretation |\r\n|--------|----------|--------------|----------------|\r\n| Invariants retained | ~60 | varies (expect ~10-15) | Compression ratio |\r\n| CFI mean | low (~0.18) | high (>=0.7) | Signal quality |\r\n| Prediction accuracy | TBD | TBD | Experimental outcome |\r\n| Noise artifacts | high | low | Contamination rate |\r\n\r\n### Implementation\r\n\r\n#### Step 1: Parse pulse history\r\n```python\r\n# Extract text from last 20 pulse_*.md files\r\n# Build invariant frequency table\r\n# Compute CFI for each invariant\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Step 2: Apply both compression strategies\r\n```python\r\nbaseline_compressed = top_k_by_frequency(invariants, k=60)\r\ncfi_compressed = [i for i in invariants if i.cfi >= 0.7]\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Step 3: Evaluate on next pulse\r\n- Use compressed invariants to predict what next pulse should contain\r\n- Compare predicted content against actual next pulse\r\n- Metrics: token overlap, semantic similarity (if LLM available)\r\n\r\n### Expected Outcomes\r\n\r\n| Scenario | Interpretation |\r\n|----------|----------------|\r\n| CFI >> Baseline accuracy | Confirm CFI selects true causal anchors |\r\n| CFI ≈ Baseline | CFI doesn't add value; frequency is sufficient |\r\n| CFI << Baseline | CFI too aggressive; losing useful patterns |\r\n\r\n### Risk Mitigation\r\n- If CFI set is too small (<5 invariants): lower threshold to 0.5\r\n- If CFI set is too large (>50): raise threshold to 0.8\r\n- Document trade-off curve for future tuning\r\n\r\n## Files to Create\r\n- `experiments/cfi_compression_test.py` - Implementation\r\n- `experiments/cfi_compression_results.md` - Output\r\n\r\n## Next Steps After Experiment\r\n1. If H1 confirmed: Implement CFI filtering in pulse.ps1\r\n2. If H2 confirmed: Add CFI=0 filtering as\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 11:25:47\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774365961657}}
